tspan.tspan: The Solution Sketch is a method used to expand upon one
solution idea (from Crazy 8â€™s.) In this exercise, each team
member spends more time articulating one idea they are most
interested in, regardless of the most popular ideas identified
from the Crazy 8â€™s sketches. The goal is to create one fully
fleshed out idea for the solution that is thought to be the best.
This should take 30-40 minutes.
01. Choose an Idea
After completing the Crazy 8â€™s exercise, select the idea from
your own or others you think is the best
02. Sketching Details
Flesh out the idea in a detailed sketch. A Solution Sketch
should include three frames or states of the concept to help
illustrate how it works, as well as a clear title to help people
remember it.
03. Be Expressive
Use multiple frames, pictures, and words in your sketch. This
will help you communicate your thoughts to the team.
04. Voting
Give each team member three votes (colored dots.) The team
will have five minutes to indicate the three most compelling
ideas by voting on the sketches they like best.
